author: Vincent Pang
text:
ANYTIME FITNESS Potong Pasir: A Solid Choice with Room for Improvement

ANYTIME FITNESS Potong Pasir offers a convenient location and a well-equipped facility. The 24/7 access is a significant perk, allowing for flexible workout schedules. The gym is generally clean and well-maintained, thanks to the diligent cleaning staff.

The staff are friendly and helpful, providing assistance when needed. However, the atmosphere could be enhanced with better music distribution, especially on the ground floor.
The free WiFi is a nice touch, but the outdated hotspot model can be frustrating. Upgrading to a regular WiFi setup with secure WEP access would significantly improve the user experience.

While the gym is accessible, the lack of a covered walkway can be a bit inconvenient on rainy days, particularly for those who park further away.

Additionally, the ground floor can get quite warm in the afternoons, especially when the sun is shining.

A few suggestions to improve the gym experience:
* Install cubbies on the ground floor: This would be convenient for members who prefer to store their belongings on the ground floor.

* Install heat film on the ground floor: This would help regulate the temperature and create a more comfortable workout environment.

* Implement stricter rules against hogging machines: Clear signage or verbal reminders could discourage members from monopolizing equipment.

* Upgrade the WiFi system: A more user-friendly WiFi system would enhance the overall gym experience.

Overall, ANYTIME FITNESS Potong Pasir is a solid choice for those seeking a well-equipped gym with flexible hours. With a few minor improvements, it could become an even more enjoyable workout destination.

author: Sihan Goi
text:
Came for a morning workout at around 730am on a Wednesday, and it was still quite empty, but got busy around an hour later. All the racks and platforms were used by then.

Equipment is quite ok, and is spread across 2 levels. Majority are on the ground floor, with 2 full power racks with attached platforms, both kg and lb bumper plates, rubberised plates, Lifefitness plate loaded machines, benches and cable machines, dumbbells up to 50kg, fixed bars, cardio equipment, etc.

Specs wise, it's pretty decent, but I have some gripes. Firstly, despite having some Rogue bars (both kg and lbs), none of the bars spin properly. Also, while there are both kg and lb bumper plates (Hammer Strength kg and Rogue lb plates), there aren't enough to support 2 racks and 2 platforms. There was only 1 set of 10-25kg plates, and 1+ set of 10-55 lb plates. Also, the floor around the racks/platforms was damp. It seems water has seeped into the rubber flooring. You can't tell from just looking at it, but once you step on it, you can see wet imprints of your shoes/feet. I wore my socks without shoes while warming up and wet it while walking around the platforms. Because of this, I had to wear my shoes later on without socks.

Another gripe is that the racks are quite short, and the J hooks can only be used internally and doesn't extend out to the platform. Because if this, if you're tall, good luck pressing inside the rack - you'll likely hit the top. The intervals between J hook positions are also fairly wide, so you may end up in a case where 1 position is too high, and the next one is too low.

Lastly, while the aircon was on and the temperature wasn't that high, I was sweating buckets due to lack of circulation. The fans were not sufficient IMHO as they didn't reach the corner racks/platforms. I don't have this problem at other AF.

There is a studio on level 2 as well as some miscellaneous equipment that seems to be haphazardly placed there.

Facilities wise, the are restrooms, 2 shower rooms with both shampoo and body wash, lockers, and open pigeon holes. These are all unisex.

Parking is very limited around the gym, I was lucky to find a lot further way since I was early, but good luck if you're not.

This gym has the potential to be 4 stars or more if the above are fixed.

author: Cassie Yu
text:
#Proceed with Caution Before Signing Up Because You DON‚ÄôT Know What You Signed Up For#

I recently had a very frustrating experience with anytime fitness Potong Pasir regarding their membership cancellation policy, and I feel compelled to share my story to help others make an informed decision.

I signed up for a membership with them on July 2024, but due to a neurological condition, I am currently under medical care and taking prescribed medication. On 25 Feb, my doctor provided me with a referral letter to a neurologist to take further examination on my disease. On 4 Mar, I have submitted that to request a cancellation of my membership, on 5 Mar I submitted another medical certificate clearly stating that I am unable to exercise for two weeks until further review, following the terms outlined in the contract.

To my surprise, they rejected my cancellation request. Their reasoning was that my membership minimum term ends in 2026, and the medical documents only state that I am unable to exercise for two weeks, which they claim is insufficient for a "Premature Cancellation." However, the contract does not specify any required duration for being unable to exercise to qualify for cancellation. I have asked to clarify their decision and provide a valid explanation, but I have yet to receive a response.

This lack of transparency and unwillingness to accommodate a legitimate medical condition is extremely frustrating and disappointing. I urge anyone considering signing up for a membership with Anytime Fitness Potong Pasir to carefully review their cancellation policy and think twice before committing, especially if you have any health concerns or relocation concerns.

I hope they will reconsider their stance and provide better support for their members in the future. Until then, I cannot recommend this gym in good conscience.

author: Elaine T
text:
My husband and I signed up for trial at two Anytime Fitness gyms, including AF Potong Pasir. These two gyms were the closest to our house.

When the club inquired, I was transparent with them that we needed to check out both locations before making a decision. As with any trial, this includes finding out the gym facilities and packages they have to offer. I presumed each gym's facilities and pricing would be different as they are independently owned.

Initially there were a lot of questions from AF Potong Pasir over text and uncertainty on their end about what to do, but they eventually rescinded the free trial and offered me a club tour instead.

In the same message, I was accused of "club-hopping without intention of signing up a membership". In their words, "This could be classified as an abuse to our system as you are utilising the free trials across multiple clubs with no definite intention to sign a membership package."

When I reiterated my intentions to them and explained the misunderstanding on their part, there was no apology from them at all and they only talked about their policies. They could have contacted me by phone call if they needed to clarify further, but they did not do so.

As customers who were ready to sign up for a new gym membership, this was downright insulting and embarrassing to say the least. To us, this is a red flag in terms of their management.

First of all, if a customer is not allowed to sign up for trial at more than one location, this should have been stated clearly on the website. If I had known, I would have only signed up for trial at one location and saved myself from being disrespected this way.

Secondly, I understand that every company has to adhere to their own terms and conditions. If you have to withdraw your free trial, that is totally fine - but at least be courteous when you are informing the person, instead of accusing them of abusing the system.

The free trial is not important here; it is their customer service or the lack thereof that is alarming. A blessing in disguise that we realised this before signing up as members at this location.

text: best gym i have been and i am doing my cutting  journey here which is going very well . night time is best time to do gym . recommended

author: Fardhanshah Shahrom
text: Been with AF for a while now, but this gym is my go to gym even though I live at sengkang with a AF gym infront my house haha. I don't feel pressured working out at this gym as the staffs are really friendly and the environment at the gym feels friendly. Cleanliness is always excellent.

author: YETI_97
text: Training chest with my friend. We were at the smith machine benching 40kg aside on the incline. I was counting out his reps and the manager came to confront us saying "understand y'all are training intense but you're making too much noise"...when we asked how come it's ok for people there to bang the weights on deadlift he said "oh because it's the weights making noise so it's allowed". Literally doesn't make sense at all... might as well put up a sign and say that this is a library and no intense training or bodybuilders allowed. Apparently people that damage gym property, don't rack back their weights, or play games on the gym equipment are more welcomed. Never coming back to this outlet again!

author: John Benedict Adhithya
text: It's big and compared to other anytime fitness, better one in cleanliness and has a huge studio for cardio but not very crowded all the time(exceptpeak hours). If you want to have a good gym pic session this is a good place to try out.

author: Shan Shan Chua
text:
Attended boot camp which is under HPB sunrise in the city programme, conducted by Jonathon.

Excellent experience, gym is clean, Jonathon really focused on the form, which is important to ensure no injuries and working on the right muscle group.

Shower facilities available, but you'll need to bring your own towels.

author: Kat
text: Super troublesome to even terminate the membership. Need to pay lots of fees and provide them letter etc. Already paying high monthly charges with not so fantastic gyms.. I would highly recommend to go Fitness First, which is way better in all aspect. Especially the one at Tanjong Pagar.

text:
Dear Bunny Lin

Greetings from Anytime Fitness Potong Pasir

Thank you for your feedback and We are so sorry about the frustration you are having.

This is not how we want any of our customers to feel and with that being said, we would like to understand further on your review.

It will be great if we can get in touch over email at potongpasir@anytimefitness.sg or contact us over at 8887 9926

We would really want to get to know the negative experience you had at our club and offer you a solution.

Our staffs are equipped with neccessary skill sets to ensure customer service is given at the highest order and we would like to apologize if there has been any short comings in that.

Hope to hear from you real soon.
